To giue a full, a cleare and satisfactory answer vnto this demand, which stumbles many: We must consider in the first place; that the glad tidings and promises of the Gospell are proper and peculiar to the elect and chosen Saints of God, and not common to the elect and reprobates as the law is, which binds all men alike: Hence is it, that the elect onely are said, Rom. 9. 7, 8. Gal. 2. 22. to be the children of the promise, the seed of Abraham, and the promise of faith by Iesus Christ; is said, to be giuen onely to them which belieue: Iohn. 10. 3, 4, 27. The voyce of Christ is proper onely to the sheepe of Christ, who are the elect: whence the faith of the Gospell is stiled Tie. 1. 1. the faith of Gods elect, as being proper and peculiar vnto them alone: Christ lesus hath Iohn. 17. 6, 8, 14, 17, 20, 26. Iude 3. bequeathed his Gospell as a peculiar legacie to his Saints and chosen ones, and deliuered and committed it to them. Wherefore the Apostles did alwaies dedicate and direct their Epistles Rom. 1. 7. 16, 1. c 8, 26 to 35 1 Cor. 1. 2. 2. Cor. 1. 1. Ephesians. 1. 1. to 15. c. 2. 1. to the end. Phil. 1. 1. Col. 1. 1. 1 Thes. 1. 1, 3, 4. 2 Thes. 1. 1. 3. ca. 2. 13, 14. 1 Pet. 1. 1. to 24. ca 2. 7, 9, 10. 2 Pet. 1. 1, 10. 2 Ioh. 3. 3 Ioh. 2. 3. Iude 1. 3. Ps. 50. 16, 17. to the elect, the chosen and faithfull in Christ Iesus; to the Saints, the sanctified, called and preserued in Christ Iesus, and to no others: to signifie that the Gospell is proper and peculiar vnto them. Secondly, you must obserue, that though the ministers of the Gospell, are to Mark. 16. 16. preach the Gospell to euery creature, yet it is not with an intent to conuert all those that heare it vnto God, but onely the elect: Paul did preach and 2 Tim. 2. 10. indure all things, not for all those to whom he preached; but onely for the elects sake;
that they might obtaine the saluation which is in Christ Iesus with eternall glory: Ephe. 4. 11, 12 God hath giuen some to bee Apostles,
some Prophets, some Euangelists, some Pastors and teachers; but this is not for the conuersion and good of all men, but it is onely for the perfecting of the Saints, and for the edifying of the body of Christ, Eph. 1 1, 4, 5, 6, 9, 10, 11, 22, 23. c 1. 7, 10, 13, 19, 21, 22 c. 5. 2 • , 29, 30. 1 Pet. 5 13 Ro. 8. 29, • 0. Hebr. 12 22, 23. who are the elect. The preachers of the Gospell who are stiled Angells, are sent out onely Matth. 24. 31. to gather the elect (not all men) from the fo • re Windes. from the one end of heauen to the other: Heb. 1, 14 Reu. 7. 3. to 16. they are all ministring spirits sent forth to minister for them (and for them only) who shall be heires of saluation; not for reprobates and wicked men: they are onley Acts. 10. 28. Ioh 21. 15, 16, 17. 2 Tim. 2. 10. to feede the Church, the lambes, the sheepe and flocke of Christ; who are onely the elect, as the Scriptures and the Fathers haue defined it: therefore the milke and foode of the word and Gospell is proper and peculiar vnto them. Thirdly, you must take notice, that though the Gospell be to be preached vnto euery creature, yet it is not with an intent to conuert & saue all those that heare it preached, but only true belieuers: this is euident by that commission which Christ gaue vnto his Apostles: Mat. 16, 15, 16. Goe yee (saith he) into all the world, and preach the Gospell to euery creature, he that belieueth, and is baptized shall bee saued, but hee that belieueth not shall bee damned: By which conditionall clause and limitation, its most apparant: that God did neuer intend that his Gospell should conuert and saue all such as heare it preached, (as is further warranted by ler. 1. 10. cap. 7. 26, 27, 28. Ezech. 2. 3. to 9, 10. Heb. 4. 2. 2 Cor. 2. 14, 15, 16) where God commanded his word to be preached to some that should not heare it nor obey it, nor reape any profit or conuersion from it:) but onely such as should belieue and imbrace it in their hearts. Now these are only the elect, and no others; for Acts. 13 48. Iohn 10. 26. Rom 8. 30. they onely doe belieue: Therefore the Gospell is intended vnto them alone.
